{"ts":"2026-04-27T14:00:00Z","op":"unlock-edit-relock","file":"scripts/bin/hexa_remote","actor":"sub-AG","change":"GPU-aware dispatch L8 admission tier — probe extension (3rd line: GPU avail MB via nvidia-smi memory.free, default 0 if absent) + classify_job '--gpu/--cuda' flag → 'gpu' class (mk10 engine also triggers gpu) + L8 admission tier rejecting class=gpu when host gpu_avail < min (default 8192MB, override HEXA_REMOTE_GPU_MIN_AVAIL_MB[_HOST]). LB=avail picker exports _picked_gpu_avail. raw 66 4-step trailer on reject: nvidia-smi inspect / lower min / disable / wait. Bypass: HEXA_REMOTE_NO_GPU_ADMISSION=1. Physical limit pairing: RTX 5070 12GB VRAM - 4GB workload buffer = 8GB threshold (raw 36 fixpoint).","reason":"/loop iteration 1 directive '자원들 물리적,수학적 한계 기준 최대한 활용' — RTX 5070×2 (ubu1+ubu2, 24GB total VRAM) was 0% utilized; cluster_load_audit (Sub-AF) surfaced gap. Adding GPU class enables drill workloads to dispatch to GPU hosts.","authority":"raw 1 + raw 66 + raw 80 + raw 85 + raw 36 problem-solving-triad fixpoint","convergence":"convergence/r4_gpu_aware_dispatch_2026_04_27.convergence","roadmap-ref":"R4_GPU_AWARE_DISPATCH","window_sec":0,"verified":"bash -n PASS post-relock; smoke kick tree dispatched without regression"}
{"ts":"2026-04-27T14:05:00Z","op":"unlock-edit-relock","file":"scripts/bin/hexa_remote","actor":"sub-AH","change":"_per_host_max() mathematical-limit dynamic compute. Old: hardcoded 1 slot per host (hetzner 122GB / 24GB-large = 4-5 mathematically-available, only 1 used = 75% capacity dormant). New: floor((avail_mb - safety_4096) / class_min_mb), clamped [1, 8]. Examples: hetzner+large 122000MB → 4 slots, ubu1+medium 25000MB → 2 slots, hetzner+small 122000MB → 8 slots (clamp). Priority: per-host env > global env > dynamic > fallback 1. _NEXUS_ORIG_ARGV stash early so dynamic compute can call _classify_job from acquire-time context.","reason":"/loop iteration 2 directive '자원들 물리적,수학적 한계 기준 최대한 활용' — Sub-AG (iteration 1) opened GPU dispatch path, Sub-AH closes RAM-headroom dispatch gap. cluster_load_audit (Sub-AF) showed hetzner 122GB avail with only 1 concurrent slot = mathematical waste. Dynamic compute matches 'mathematical limit' framing precisely (queuing theory: capacity = floor(resource / per-job-cost)).","authority":"raw 1 + raw 36 problem-solving-triad fixpoint + raw 66 + raw 85","convergence":"convergence/r4_per_host_dynamic_concurrency_2026_04_27.convergence","roadmap-ref":"R4_PER_HOST_DYNAMIC_CONCURRENCY","window_sec":0,"verified":"bash -n PASS post-relock; smoke kick tree did not regress dispatch path"}
{"ts":"2026-04-27T14:10:00Z","op":"unlock-edit-relock","file":"scripts/bin/hexa_remote","actor":"sub-AI","change":"_per_host_max dynamic clamp PSI-aware. Old: uniform clamp [1, 8]. New: clamp = max(1, 8 - floor(PSI/12)) where PSI is the probe-captured _best_psi. Math mapping: PSI 0→8, 24→6, 48→4, 72→2, 84+→1. Bypass HEXA_REMOTE_NO_PSI_CLAMP=1. Effect: hetzner avail=122GB PSI=97% would have allowed 4 slots (Sub-AH dynamic) but PSI clamp reduces to 1 — physical pressure signal as ceiling. hetzner same avail PSI=30% → clamp 6 → dynamic 4 wins (clamp = ceiling, not floor). ubu1 avail=25GB PSI=0% → dynamic 2 unchanged.","reason":"/loop iteration 3 directive '자원들 물리적,수학적 한계 기준' — PSI signal IS the physical limit ground truth (memory pressure stall %). Sub-AH dynamic compute used avail-RAM proxy; Sub-AI adds PSI direct signal. Closed-form mathematical mapping clamp=f(PSI) — Banach-style fixpoint between dispatcher decision and physical pressure feedback.","authority":"raw 1 + raw 36 fixpoint + raw 66 + raw 85","convergence":"inline (commit message + this audit row — atomic 5min budget, no separate convergence file this iter)","roadmap-ref":"R4_PSI_AWARE_CLAMP","window_sec":0,"verified":"bash -n PASS post-relock; math verification 6 PSI points (0/24/48/72/84/95) → expected clamp values"}
