{"ts":"2026-04-27T14:20:00Z","op":"unlock-edit-relock","file":"scripts/bin/hexa_remote","actor":"sub-AK","change":"GPU concurrent slot tracking — Sub-AG L8 admission was single-shot avail check (over-commit risk). Add _per_host_gpu_max + _acquire_gpu_slot parallel to RAM L1 _per_host_max + _acquire_slot. Lock prefix /tmp/nexus_gpu_dispatch.<host>.gpu_slot<N>.lock. Math: floor((gpu_avail-1024)/4096), clamp [1,4]. RTX 5070 11500MB free / 4GB inference = 2 slots/host (was 1). Trap merges _ACQUIRED + _GPU_ACQUIRED for atomic dual release on EXIT. Override: HEXA_REMOTE_GPU_CONCURRENCY[_HOST] / HEXA_REMOTE_GPU_PER_JOB_VRAM_MB / HEXA_REMOTE_GPU_SAFETY_MB / HEXA_REMOTE_NO_GPU_CONCURRENCY=1.","reason":"/loop iteration 5 directive '자원들 물리적,수학적 한계 기준' — Sub-AG opened GPU dispatch path with single-shot admission (no concurrency cap). Sub-AK adds slot tracking parallel to RAM L1 closing the over-commit gap. RTX 5070×2 (24GB total VRAM) physical limit utilized: 2 slots × 2 hosts = 4 concurrent GPU jobs cluster-wide.","authority":"raw 1 + raw 36 fixpoint + raw 66 + raw 80 + raw 85","convergence":"convergence/r4_gpu_concurrent_slot_2026_04_27.convergence","roadmap-ref":"R4_GPU_CONCURRENT_SLOT","window_sec":0,"verified":"bash -n PASS post-relock; math 6 (vram, per_job) pairs → expected slot counts; trap composition tested (single trap with both vars)"}
